To evaluate the efficacy of increasing temperature and light intensity in accurately predicting the stability of the OPVs under standard reporting conditions (1 sun intensity, AM1.5 G spectrum, 25 °C)28, the cells are exposed to light intensity to up to 27 suns using white light-emitting diodes (LEDs, see Methods). Provided that the effects of temperature and intensity on device aging are independent, the degradation acceleration factor given by28:1A=ItestIrefγexp−EakB1Ttest−1Ta\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
